IT was really a celebration of the best at the Best of the Best Pageant hosted by Modelling Motions on Saturday, 25 June. Tholang Lebelo, CEO of the venture, said the pageant was a way of giving young people an opportunity to show their talent. The event was hosted at Chief Mogale Hall in Kagiso, Mogale City. Winners walked away with bursaries to study a computer course. READ: Miss SA returns to Gauteng! “We want to empower young girls by making sure that their passion gives them a better future, which is why our winners won bursaries,” he said. Miss Best of the Best has five categories the Little, Juniors, Pre-Teen, Teenagers and Seniors. Miss Teen Queen Shamiso Biza (16) said modelling was her safe space. The Queen won a course worth R7 000, the first runner-up won a course worth R5 999 and the second runner-up won a course worth R1 299. The pageants were sponsored by Axuxeni Computer Academy and Ntimane Construction.